Class IndexedAccessor

java.lang.Object

          org.jcatapult.mvc.parameter.el.IndexedAccessor

public class IndexedAccessor
extends MemberAccessor

This models a indexed property that takes a single parameter for the getter that is the index or key and two parameters for the setter, the index/key and value.

Author:
Brian Pontarelli

isIndexed

public boolean isIndexed()
Overrides:
isIndexed in class MemberAccessor
Returns:
Always false. The reason is that since this invokes the indexed property, we want it to look like a non-indexed property so that the context will invoke the method.
